When trying to define a user macro containing an a-tag for styling purposes, the a-tag receives a css-class

When trying to write a user macro containing an a-tag with a custom class 
{code}<a class="example-class" href="$paramlink">$paramtext</a>{code}

If a user includes a link to a wiki page there is no problem since no class is set for internal links but if one adds a link to it "www.google.com" into the macro then Confluence detects that as an external link and therefore adds the class "external-link" to the a-tag.

expected behaviour : the css class should not be lost when external link is being added like the code below {code} <a class="example-class external-link" href="foo">bar</a>{code}

current behaviour: the css class is lost if external links is added {code}<a class="external-link" href="foo">bar</a>{code}

