I would like to be able to copy the content from an email (including images) using an email client (Outlook, Thunderbird or others) and paste the content into a Confluence new page. Currently, when I try to perform this action, the images copied from the email are not displayed.

What I am currently doing as workaround is to copy each image, cropping it down and then paste the images into Confluence page. It would be nice if I could create a new page on Confluence and then just copy and paste the email content with the images being displayed.
